==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Linnaeus
<hw>Linnaeus</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧*n⟦emac⟧"⟦ucr⟧s)</pr> <pos>n.</pos>
<def><person>Carolus Linnaeus</person>, also called <altname>Karl von
Linn⟦eacute⟧</altname>. Born at R⟦aring⟧shult, Sm⟦aring⟧land, Sweden,
May 13, 1707: died at Upsala, Sweden, Jan. 10, 1778. A celebrated
Swedish botanist and naturalist, founder of the <er>Linnean system</er>
in botany. He made a journey to Lapland in 1732; resided in the
Netherlands 1735-38; and became professor of medicine (later of botany)
at Upsala in 1741. Among his works are ⟦ldquo⟧Systema natur⟦ae⟧⟦rdquo⟧
(1735), ⟦ldquo⟧Fundamenta botanica⟦rdquo⟧ (1736), ⟦ldquo⟧Genera
plantarum⟦rdquo⟧ (1737), ⟦ldquo⟧Flora lapponica⟦rdquo⟧ (1737),
⟦ldquo⟧Philosophia botanica⟦rdquo⟧ (1751), and ⟦ldquo⟧Species
plantarum⟦rdquo⟧ (1753).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Century Dict. 1906</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Linnaea borealis</ent>⟦br⟧
